8uhzTGK_wr2xpxeemk0g","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"H → Head Impulse Test\\N(Prueba de impulso cefálico)","guid":"euqhs1RMDSxgudo-TD7DNA","children":[{"id":"55","parent":"54","text":"NORMAL en lesión central → NO puede mantener fijación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"54","text":"ANORMAL (sacada) en lesión periférica → VOR deficiente ipsilateral","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"57","parent":"53","text":"N → Nystagmus\\N(Tipo de nistagmo)","guid":"QaX0pEAHUH4z-n31RmdsrA","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"UNIDIRECCIONAL horizontal-torsional → periférico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"DIRECCIÓN CAMBIANTE con mirada → CENTRAL (signo de alarma)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"57","text":"Suprimido con fijación → periférico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"57","text":"NO suprimido con fijación → central","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"57","text":"Vertical puro | torsional puro → SIEMPRE central","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"53","text":"T → Test of Skew\\N(Skew deviation)","guid":"aFLBh2BPIiF8K3ITFyh9_Q","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"Cover-uncover test → desviación vertical ocular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"63","text":"POSITIVO (desviación) → central (lesión otolítica-tronco)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"66","parent":"53","text":"HINTS CENTRAL si CUALQUIERA de: HIT normal + nistagmo dirección cambiante + skew (+)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"53","text":"Sensibilidad 100%, especificidad 96% para ACV en síndrome vestibular agudo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"53","text":"SUPERA DWI-MRI en primeras 48h (falsos negativos MRI ~12-15%)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"69","parent":"52","text":"Marcha y\\Nequilibrio","guid":"GaB3rRgxniwq-J9QODGLFg","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"Periférico → puede caminar (mal pero puede)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71",