| ataxia ipsilateral | disfagia | disfonía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"144","text":"Nistagmo + dirección cambiante según posición","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"144","text":"Frecuentemente subestimado → buscar activamente en AM con FR","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"149","parent":"102","text":"TIA vertebrobasilar","guid":"","children":[{"id":"150","parent":"149","text":"Vértigo aislado transitorio <1h con FR vasculares → considerar TIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"149","text":"Riesgo ACV 8-14% a 2 años según número de FR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"149","text":"Estudio completo → RMN + angiografía + ecocardio","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"102","text":"Hipotensión ortostática (CRÍTICO en AM)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"Causa frecuente en AM subestimada como mareo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"Caída PAS ≥20mmHg o PAD ≥10mmHg al 1-3 min bípedo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"Causas → deshidratación | polifarmacia (antihipertensivos | diuréticos | dopaminérgicos)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"153","text":"SIEMPRE medir PA ortostática en AM con mareo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"158","parent":"102","text":"PPPD (Mareo Postural Perceptual Persistente)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"159","parent":"158","text":"Mareo crónico funcional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"158","text":"Exacerbado por ambientes visuales complejos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"158","text":"Comórbido con ansiedad/depresión (>40%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"158","text":"TCC + rehabilitación vestibular","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"163","parent":"102","text":"Fármacos en AM","guid":"","children":[{"id":"164","parent":"163","text":"Aminoglicósidos → vestibulopía bilateral (sin vértigo, sí desequilibrio + oscilopsía)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"163","text":"BZD | antiepilépticos | antihipertensivos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"163","text":"Revisar STOPP en todo AM con mareo de inicio/empeoramiento","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"167","parent":"0","text":"TRATAMIENTO EN SU","guid":"","children":[{"id":"168","parent":"167","text":"Supresores vestibulares (SOLO primeras 24-48h)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"Indicación → vértigo severo agudo (no VPPB)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"ANTIHISTAMÍNICOS → primera línea (evidencia metaanálisis 17 RCT)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"Dimenhidrinato IV 50mg → eficacia similar a lorazepam con menos sedación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"170","text":"Meclizina oral 25-50mg","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"173","parent":"168","text":"ANTIEMETICOS (náuseas severas / vómitos)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"Ondansetron 4-8mg IV/SL → menos efectos extrapiramidales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"173","text":"Metoclopramida 10mg IV → eficaz, riesgo extrapiramidalismo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"173","text":"Proclorperazina → más sedante","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"177","parent":"168","text":"BENZODIAZEPINAS → alternativa, NO primera línea","guid":"","children":[{"id":"178","parent":"177","text":"Lorazepam 1-2mg → más sedación, peor marcha vs dimenhidrinato","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"177","text":"EVITAR en AM → riesgo caída, confusión, delirium","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"168","text":"SUSPENDER a las 48h → retrasan compensación central","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"181","parent":"167","text":"Maniobra de Epley (VPPB canal posterior)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"Efectividad única sesión → 85%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"Sin restricción postural posterior (no agrega beneficio)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"181","text":"Enseñar autoEpley al alta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"181","text":"Vitamina D → suplementar si <20ng/mL → reduce recurrencia (RR 0.76)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"186","parent":"167","text":"NO USAR en neuritis vestibular","guid":"","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"Corticoides → no mejoran outcomes clínicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"186","text":"Antivirales → sin evidencia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"189","parent":"167","text":"Rehabilitación vestibular","guid":"","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"Iniciar PRECOZ post 48h en neuritis vestibular → evidencia GRADO 2B","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"189","text":"Inicio temprano = mejor outcome (período crítico primeras semanas)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"192","parent":"0","text":"CONSIDERACIONES GERIÁTRICAS ESPECÍFICAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"193","parent":"192","text":"FRAGILIDAD → modifica presentación y outcomes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"Mayor riesgo de caída y fractura durante episodio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"193","text":"Compensación central más lenta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"193","text":"Recuperación más prolongada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"197","parent":"192","text":"POLIFARMACIA → causa frecuente y modificable","guid":"","children":[{"id":"198","parent":"197","text":"STOPP/START al ingreso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"197","text":"Carga anticolinérgica → empeora equilibrio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"197","text":"Antihipertensivos → hipotensión ortostática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"197","text":"BZD → EVITAR como supresores vestibulares","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"202","parent":"192","text":"DELIRIUM → complicación / diagnóstico diferencial","guid":"","children":[{"id":"203","parent":"202","text":"Vértigo puede precipitar delirium en AM frágil","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"202","text":"Delirium puede simular vértigo (desorientación espacial)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"202","text":"Usar CAM en AM confuso con mareo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"206","parent":"192","text":"CAÍDAS → consecuencia principal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"207","parent":"206","text":"Evaluar riesgo de caída al alta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"206","text":"Prescribir rehabilitación vestibular como prevención","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"206","text":"Timed Up and Go (TUG) como marcador pronóstico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"210","parent":"192","text":"HIPOACUSIA CONCOMITANTE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"211","parent":"210","text":"Dificulta anamnesis (comunicación)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"210","text":"Aumenta riesgo de desequilibrio (multisensorial)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"213","parent":"192","text":"DIABETES → modifica presentación ACV","guid":"","children":[{"id":"214","parent":"213","text":"Infartos lacunares silentes previos → foco neurológico atípico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"213","text":"Neuropatía periférica contribuye a desequilibrio","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"216","parent":"192","text":"FIBRILACIÓN AURICULAR → FR mayor ACV cardioembólico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"217","parent":"216","text":"Vértigo agudo + FA → descartar ACV urgente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"216","text":"Revisar anticoagulación","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"219","parent":"0","text":"CRITERIOS DE HOSPITALIZACIÓN","guid":"Wk1WMH-y4ApM9QcEOmHFnA","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"HOSPITALIZAR si","guid":"","children":[{"id":"221","parent":"220","text":"HINTS central → todo paciente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"220","text":"No puede caminar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"223","parent":"220","text":"Sospecha ACV o TIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"224","parent":"220","text":"Vómitos incoercibles con deshidratación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"225","parent":"220","text":"Caída con lesión | fractura","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"220","text":"AM frágil sin soporte en domicilio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"220","text":"Primera crisis Ménière severa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"228","parent":"219","text":"OBSERVACIÓN si","guid":"","children":[{"id":"229","parent":"228","text":"Síntomas en regresión con tratamiento + control en 48h asegurado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"230","parent":"219","text":"ALTA con","guid":"","children":[{"id":"231","parent":"230","text":"Diagnóstico periférico claro","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"230","text":"Control ambulatorio pactado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"230","text":"Educación sobre restricciones (conducción vehículos)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"230","text":"AutoEpley enseñado si VPPB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"235","parent":"230","text":"Instrucciones retorno → signos de alarma central","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"236","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"237","parent":"236","text":"HINTS > MRI-DWI en primeras 48h → no depender de imagen para descartar ACV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"238","parent":"236","text":"En AM con mareo → SIEMPRE medir PA ortostática antes de plantear etiología vestibular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"239","parent":"236","text":"NEVER diagnose BPPV in a patient with sustained vertigo at rest → busca HINTS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"236","text":"BZD CONTRAINDICADAS como supresor vestibular en AM → caída + delirium + retrasa compensación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"236","text":"Neuritis vestibular: suspender supresores a 48h → rehabilitar precoz → evidencia GRADO 2B","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"236","text":"Infarto cerebeloso hasta 25% de >50a con vértigo agudo en SU → umbral bajo para MRI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"243","parent":"236","text":"Nistagmo que cambia de dirección con la mirada = CENTRAL hasta demostrar lo contrario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"244","parent":"236","text":"HIT anormal (sacada) = lesión periférica / HIT normal en vértigo agudo sostenido = ALARMA CENTRAL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"236","text":"Wallenberg → frecuentemente subestimado → buscar Horner + hipoestesia facial + disfagia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"236","text":"FA + vértigo agudo = infarto cardioembólico cerebeloso hasta demostrar lo contrario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"247","parent":"236","text":"Vitamina D → suplementar en AM con VPPB recurrente si nivel <20ng/mL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"248","parent":"236","text":"Rehabilitación vestibular temprana → previene caídas + PPPD posneuritis","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"249","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"250","parent":"249","text":"1. Furman JM, Barton JJS. Evaluation of the patient with vertigo. UpToDate. Topic 5094 Version 21.0. 2025.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"251","parent":"249","text":"2. Furman JM. Vestibular neuritis and labyrinthitis. UpToDate. Topic 5102 Version 13.0. 2024.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"252","parent":"249","text":"3. Furman JM, Barton JJS. Treatment of vertigo. UpToDate. Topic 5097 Version 19.0. 2025.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"253","parent":"249","text":"4. Barton JJS. Benign paroxysmal positional vertigo. UpToDate. Topic 5098 Version 26.0. 2024.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"254","parent":"249","text":"5. Robertson CE, Eggers SD. Vestibular migraine. UpToDate. Topic 3356 Version 34.0. 2025.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"249","text":"6. Caplan LR. Posterior circulation cerebrovascular syndromes. UpToDate. Topic 1102 Version 28.0. 2024.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"256","parent":"249","text":"7. Kattah JC, Talkad AV, Wang DZ, et al. HINTS to diagnose stroke in the acute vestibular syndrome. Stroke. 2009;40(11):3504-10.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"257","parent":"249","text":"8. Norrving B, Magnusson M, Holtas S. Isolated acute vertigo in the elderly; vestibular or vascular disease? Acta Neurol Scand. 1995;91(1):43-7.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"258","parent":"249","text":"9. Hunter BR, Wang AZ, Bucca AW, et al. Efficacy of benzodiazepines or antihistamines for patients with acute vertigo. JAMA Neurol. 2022;79(8):846-54.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"259","parent":"249","text":"10. Tinetti ME, Williams CS, Gill TM. Dizziness among older adults: a possible geriatric syndrome. Ann Intern Med. 2000;132(5):337-44.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"260","parent":"249","text":"11. Strupp M, Bisdorff A, Furman J, et al. Acute unilateral vestibulopathy/vestibular neuritis: diagnostic criteria. J Vestib Res. 2022;32(5):389-406.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":260,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Geriatría","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Geriatría","filename":"Vertigo_Urgencias_Geriatria_iPad","id":"map_1016","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Vertigo_Urgencias_Geriatria_iPad"}